###Main VCS Components:-
1. HAD (High availabilty daemon)
Responsibilities:
  Monitors resources
  Detects failures
  Performs failover

2. LLT (Low Latency Transport)
Provides heartbeat communication between cluster nodes.
If heartbeat stops, VCS suspects a node failure.
lltstat -nvv

3. GAB (Group Membership Service)
Tracks cluster membership.
Determines:
Which nodes are alive?
Which nodes left the cluster?
gabconfig -a

Q: What does 'Node1 loses heartbeat with Node2' mean?
Node1 loses heartbeat
Node2 loses heartbeat
It does not necessarily mean both servers are down.
It means the cluster communication between the nodes has been interrupted.
Heartbeat loss means cluster nodes can no longer communicate through the LLT heartbeat network. The nodes themselves
may still be running, but each node may assume the other has failed. This can lead to a split-brain condition where 
multiple nodes try to access the same shared resources.
VCS uses I/O fencing and coordinator disks to ensure only one node retains access to shared storage and continues 
providing services.


4. I/O Fencing
Protects shared storage from split-brain situations.
Node1 loses heartbeat
Node2 loses heartbeat

Both nodes might think they are active.
Data corruption

I/O fencing ensures only one node can access shared storage.

