Interview Answer (2-Minute Version)
VCS is a high-availability clustering solution from Veritas that monitors applications, storage, network resources,
and servers. It uses LLT and GAB for cluster communication and HAD as the cluster engine. If a node or application fails,
VCS automatically fails over the service group to another node. For example, if an Oracle database running on Node1 crashes,
VCS imports the disk group, mounts the filesystem, brings up the virtual IP, and starts Oracle on Node2,
minimizing downtime. I/O fencing is used to prevent split-brain and protect shared storage from corruption.

